---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy" description="What Qazaq Lens collects, what it avoids collecting and how correction reports are stored.">
  <article class="wrap article-shell"><p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p><h1>Minimal data by design.</h1><div class="article-body">
    <h2>Normal reading</h2><p>The site does not use advertising trackers, fingerprinting, user accounts or behavioural profiles. Cloudflare may process technical request data required to deliver and protect the site.</p>
    <h2>Correction reports</h2><p>When the correction database is connected, the form stores the page URL, issue, reasoning, supporting source, optional suggested wording, optional name and optional email. Do not submit sensitive personal information.</p>
    <h2>Local preferences</h2><p>Your theme choice and offline cache are stored on your own device. They are not sent to Qazaq Lens.</p>
    <h2>Retention</h2><p>Correction reports should be deleted when no longer needed for editorial review. Public change histories describe accepted corrections without publishing private contact details.</p>
    <h2>Contact</h2><p>Use the <a href="/report-error">correction form</a> for content and privacy concerns.</p>
  </div></article>
</BaseLayout>
